label.value: adult wedge projection neuron 6

value.value: Adult neuron that has dendritic arborizations in the wedge and lateral horn and also has an axon in the lateral horn (Dolan et al., 2019; Bates et al., 2020). It is a secondary neuron that is part of the VPNp&v1 (BLP1) posterior hemilineage (Bates et al., 2020). They are GABAergic (Dolan et al., 2019).

label.value: adult posterior ventral primary neurite tract 12

value.value: Twelfth primary neurite tract of the posterior ventral (PV) adult brain that enters the lateral horn (Dolan et al., 2019).

label.value: adult CREa1 lineage clone

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast CREa1 (BAmd1) (Yu et al., 2013). There are differences between the male and female clones (Yu et al., 2013).

label.value: neuroblast SMPad1

value.value: Neuroblast of the brain that generates a sexually-dimorphic lineage with prominent proximal neurite elaboration in the superior medial protocerebrum (Yu et al., 2013).

label.value: adult SMPad1 lineage clone

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad1 (Yu et al., 2013). There are differences between the male and female clones (Yu et al., 2013).

label.value: adult SMPad1 lineage neuron

value.value: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult (FBbt:00003004) and develops from some neuroblast SMPad1 (FBbt:00049463).

label.value: adult CREa1 lineage neuron

value.value: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult (FBbt:00003004) and develops from some neuroblast BAmd1 (FBbt:00100551).

label.value: adult FLAa3 lineage neuron

value.value: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult (FBbt:00003004) and develops from some neuroblast BAmas2 (FBbt:00100556).

label.value: adult upper Malpighian tubule

value.value: Distal portion of the adult Malpighian tubule comprising the initial, transitional and main segments (Wang and Spradling, 2020). It contains type II (stellate) cells, but no stem cells (Wang and Spradling, 2020).

label.value: adult stem cell zone of Malpighian tubule

value.value: Proximal portion of the adult Malpighian tubule comprising the lower tubule and ureter (Wang and Spradling, 2020). It contains stem cells, but no type II (stellate) cells (Wang and Spradling, 2020).

label.value: adult lower ureter

value.value: Proximal region of the ureter. It has smaller principal cells than the upper ureter (Wang and Spradling, 2020).

label.value: adult upper ureter

value.value: Distal region of the adult ureter. It has larger principal cells than the lower ureter (Wang and Spradling, 2020).

label.value: adult Malpighian tubule bar-shaped cell of initial segment

value.value: Any adult Malpighian tubule bar-shaped cell (FBbt:00047103) that is part of some adult initial segment of Malpighian tubule (FBbt:00005729).

definition.value: The change in Type II cell shape from cuboidal to bar-shaped (initial and transitional segments) or stellate-shaped (main segment) occurs in the last 12h of pupal development (Denholm, 2013).

label.value: adult Malpighian tubule bar-shaped cell of transitional segment

value.value: Any adult Malpighian tubule bar-shaped cell (FBbt:00047103) that is part of some adult transitional segment of Malpighian tubule (FBbt:00005730).

definition.value: The change in Type II cell shape from cuboidal to bar-shaped (initial and transitional segments) or stellate-shaped (main segment) occurs in the last 12h of pupal development (Denholm, 2013).

label.value: adult Malpighian tubule principal cell of initial segment

value.value: Any Malpighian tubule Type I cell (FBbt:00005796) that is part of some adult initial segment of Malpighian tubule (FBbt:00005729).

label.value: adult Malpighian tubule principal cell of transitional segment

value.value: Any Malpighian tubule Type I cell (FBbt:00005796) that is part of some adult transitional segment of Malpighian tubule (FBbt:00005730).

label.value: adult Malpighian tubule principal cell of main segment

value.value: Any Malpighian tubule Type I cell (FBbt:00005796) that is part of some adult main segment of Malpighian tubule (FBbt:00005731).

definition.value: Can be identified by expression of Urate oxidase (Wang and Spradling, 2020).

label.value: adult Malpighian tubule principal cell of lower segment

value.value: Any Malpighian tubule Type I cell (FBbt:00005796) that is part of some adult lower segment of Malpighian tubule (FBbt:00047099).

label.value: adult Malpighian tubule principal cell of lower ureter

value.value: Principal cell of the adult Malpighian tubule that is found in the lower tubule (Wang and Spradling, 2020). It is smaller and less polyploid than more distal cells in the stem cell zone (Wang and Spradling, 2020).

label.value: adult Malpighian tubule principal cell of upper ureter

value.value: Any Malpighian tubule Type I cell (FBbt:00005796) that is part of some adult upper ureter (FBbt:00049471).

label.value: adult renoblast

value.value: Non-proliferative cell that arises from the division of a renal stem cell in the adult Malpighian tubule stem cell zone (Singh et al., 2007; Wang and Spradling, 2020). It differentiates into a principal cell that stays within the stem cell zone (Wang and Spradling, 2020).

label.value: adult Malpighian tubule principal cell of stem cell zone

value.value: Principal cell of the adult Malpighian tubule that is found in the stem cell zone (ureter and lower tubule) (Wang and Spradling, 2020). Cells of the lower ureter are smaller and less polyploid than more distal cells in this region (Wang and Spradling, 2020).

label.value: adult Malpighian tubule principal cell of upper tubule

value.value: Any Malpighian tubule Type I cell (FBbt:00005796) that is part of some adult upper Malpighian tubule (FBbt:00049468).

label.value: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm-DRA1

value.value: Distal medullary amacrine neuron that arborizes in layer M6, where it receives input from approximately 9 R7 photoreceptor cells of the dorsal rim area of the retina, but not photoreceptors outside of the dorsal rim area (Sancer et al., 2019; Kind et al., 2021). These cells also form presynaptic sites just below M6 (Sancer et al., 2019; Kind et al., 2021). They vary in morphology based on their position (Sancer et al., 2019).

label.value: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm-DRA2

value.value: Distal medullary amacrine neuron that arborizes in layer M6, where it receives input from approximately 9 R8 photoreceptor cells of the dorsal rim area of the retina, but not photoreceptors outside of the dorsal rim area (Sancer et al., 2019; Kind et al., 2021). These cells do not project deeper than M6, but have vertical projections, extending upwards from M6, following incoming R8 terminals (Sancer et al., 2019). They vary in morphology based on their position (Sancer et al., 2019).

label.value: adult VNC perineurial glial cell

value.value: Perineurial glial cell of the adult ventral nerve cord. These cells have a varied morphology, ranging from elongated to square-shaped, with orientation mostly along the medial-lateral axis (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult optic lobe perineurial glial cell

value.value: Perineurial glial cell of the adult optic lobe. These cells form long thin strips along the dorsal-ventral axis (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult PNS perineurial glial cell

value.value: Perineurial glial cell of the peripheral nervous system. Each cell forms a narrow strip along the long axis of the nerve, without covering its entire circumference (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult PNS subperineurial glial cell

value.value: Subperineurial glial cell of the peripheral nervous system. These cells can individually form elongated tubes around small peripheral nerves, but larger nerves are enclosed by multiple subperineurial cells (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult central brain cell body glial cell

value.value: Glial cell of the adult that is associated with the cell body rind of the central brain. One cell can wrap around 20 to 100 cell bodies, but some cell bodies are wrapped by two neighboring glial cells (Kremer et al., 2017). They have an overall globular shape with fine lamellae protruding into surrounding areas (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult synaptic neuropil ensheathing glial cell

value.value: Glial cell of the adult central nervous system that elaborates along the outer surface of a synaptic neuropil region (Kremer et al., 2017). These cells vary in morphology as they ensheath and project complex and fine protrusions into the neuropil domains (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult tract neuropil ensheathing glial cell

value.value: Glial cell of the adult central nervous system that lies along the surface of a tract (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult central brain synaptic neuropil ensheathing glial cell

value.value: Glial cell of the adult central brain that elaborates along the outer surface of a synaptic neuropil region (Kremer et al., 2017). These cells vary in morphology as they ensheath and project complex and fine protrusions into the neuropil domains (Kremer et al., 2017). They mostly accompany neuronal branches, but occasionally also tracheal branches, into the neuropil (Kremer et al., 2017). Their nuclei are found at neuropil boundaries throughout the brain, not just adjacent to the cell body rind (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult central brain tract neuropil ensheathing glial cell

value.value: Glial cell of the adult central brain that lies along the surface of a tract (Kremer et al., 2017). These cells extend along the long axes of their tracts and have ragged ends, but together with their neighbors, they form a neatly contiguous sheath, completely surrounding the tracts (Kremer et al., 2017). Their nuclei are found in non-cortical regions deep within the brain and along the tracts they associate with (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult chalice perineurial glial cell

value.value: Perineurial glial cell of the adult optic lobe that overlies the outer perimeter of the lamina, following its chalice-like shape (Edwards and Meinertzhagen, 2010; Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult chalice subperineurial glial cell

value.value: Subperineurial glial cell of the adult optic lobe that overlies the outer perimeter of the lamina, following its chalice-like shape (Edwards and Meinertzhagen, 2010; Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult medulla astrocyte-like glial cell

value.value: Astrocyte-like (reticular) glial cell located in the adult medulla neuropil. There are at least three subtypes and they show tiling and have a high structural density (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult medulla ensheathing glial cell

value.value: Ensheathing glial cell located in the adult medulla neuropil. There are at least two subtypes, forming a dense sheath around the distal medulla and serpentine layer, where their cell bodies are found (Kremer et al., 2017). Rather than having its own ensheathing glia, the proximal medulla is invaded by fine processes from the inner chiasm glia (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult medulla cell body glial cell

value.value: Glial cell located in the cell body rind of the medulla. It is similar to cell body glial cells of the central brain (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult distal medulla ensheathing glial cell

value.value: Ensheathing glial cell of the distal adult medulla. These cells are organized as highly columnar structures and show a characteristic branching pattern in M3 and M6, where photoreceptors R8 and R7 terminate, and in M7, the serpentine layer (Kremer et al., 2017). They form a dense sheath (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult serpentine medulla ensheathing glial cell

value.value: Ensheathing glial cell with its soma in the serpentine layer of the adult medulla (Kremer et al., 2017). It sends columnar branches into both the distal and proximal medulla (Kremer et al., 2017). These cells form a dense sheath (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult lobula complex astrocyte-like glial cell

value.value: Astrocyte-like (reticular) glial cell with its soma at the surface of either the adult lobula or lobula plate (lobula complex) neuropil regions (Kremer et al., 2017). These cells take many shapes and sizes and may form branches into one or both neuropils (Kremer et al., 2017).

definition.value: Cells additionally projecting into the medulla are mentioned, but not shown in images or diagram, by Kremer et al. (2017). Not clear if these should fall under this class - part_of may need revising - https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705.

label.value: adult lobula complex ensheathing glial cell

value.value: Ensheathing glial cell with its soma at the surface of the either the lobula or lobula plate (lobula complex) neuropil regions (Kremer et al., 2017). These cells form columnar processes perpendicular to the neuropil margin, as well as tangential processes parallel to the margin (Kremer et al., 2017). They form a complex three-dimensional arrangement of branches (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult antennal lobe ensheathing glial cell

value.value: Ensheathing glial cell that forms part of the glial sheath of the antennal lobe (Kremer et al., 2017). These cells form a nearly contiguous sheet at the surface of the antennal lobe, with small holes that may be neuronal entry points (Kremer et al., 2017). They send extensions between glomeruli, following neuronal processes (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult antennal lobe astrocyte-like glial cell

value.value: Adult astrocyte-like glial cell that projects into the antennal lobe (Kremer et al., 2017). Each cell can invade multiple glomeruli and there is no difference in glial extension density between different glomeruli (Kremer et al., 2017).

definition.value: Cells might additionally branch into other neuropil domains.

label.value: adult antennal lobe cell body glial cell

value.value: Glial cell that is found in the cell body rind of the adult antennal lobe (Kremer et al., 2017). These cells enclose the cell bodies of local and projection neurons of the antennal lobe (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult mushroom body cell body glial cell

value.value: Glial cell that is found in the cell body rind of the adult mushroom body (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: adult mushroom body astrocyte-like glial cell

value.value: Adult astrocyte-like glial cell that projects into the mushroom body (Kremer et al., 2017). Glial process density is low in the synapse-rich regions of the calyx and lobes; processes show thin branches with local thickenings at various positions within their network (Kremer et al., 2017).

definition.value: Cells might additionally branch into other neuropil domains.

label.value: adult mushroom body ensheathing glial cell

value.value: Ensheathing glial cell that forms part of the glial sheath of the mushroom body (Kremer et al., 2017). These cells also form protrusions into the mushroom body, enwrapping neuronal processes (Kremer et al., 2017).

label.value: optic lobe-calycal tract 1 neuron

value.value: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that fasciculates with some adult optic lobe-calycal tract 1 (FBbt:00048337).
